occasions! I know a lot of home educators whose children are involved in: music lessons, ballet, drama, St John Ambulance groups, Guiding and Scouting etc etc. Children who are home educated are far more articulate than their schooled peers, they have great confidence and they can socialise perfectly well with all ages whereas schooled children tend to stick to their peer group. Where in the world of business do you see an office full of 18 year olds and another full of 26 year olds - you don't! &#10;People who mention socialisation as a plus for schooling really should look at the product the schools churn out! How many 'hoodies' are home educated? How many pregnant 14 years olds are home educated? How many young people who knife their peers are home educated? How many underage drinkers/binge drinkers are home educated? How many smokers are home educated? Need I go on? &#10;Before using fallacious arguments people really need to look at the evidence and get their facts straight! "/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="1284" language="en" documentId="1043" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="dizzycoolbabe" date="07 November 2009 8:03pm" docType="artcomment" origUrl="http://discussion.theguardian.com/comment-permalink/6757315" topic="homeschooling" thumbsUp="5" thumbsDown="0" origId="1043" notes="" title="Ridiculous rules for home schools"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="798"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="43" sofa="1" begin="799" end="1176"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="47" sofa="1" begin="1177" end="1284"/><types:PersuasivenessAnnotationMetaData xmi:id="51" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" annotator="annotator1" isPersuasive="true" labelDetailed="P1" isGold="false" comment="&quot;Home educators do not lock their children in cupboards all day and only bring them out on special occasions!&quot;&#13;&#10;&#13;&#10;&quot;Children who are home educated are far more articulate than